# GitHub auto-publish

When you finish implementation tasks in this repository, publish changes to GitHub before ending the turn when the user has asked for automatic publishing or when meaningful code/docs changes were made.

## Publish command

```bash
./scripts/publish-to-github.sh
```

## Behavior

- Creates `https://github.com/<owner>/shadow-llm-proxy` if it does not exist
- Pushes to `origin` if the repository or remote already exists
- Auto-commits uncommitted tracked/untracked files (respecting `.gitignore`) before push

## Authentication (required once)

Either:

```bash
gh auth login
```

Or set a token:

```bash
export GH_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here
```

## Optional environment variables

| Variable | Default | Purpose |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `GITHUB_REPO_NAME` | `shadow-llm-proxy` | Repository name |
| `GITHUB_REPO_VISIBILITY` | `public` | `public` or `private` |
| `GITHUB_BRANCH` | `main` | Branch to push |
| `GITHUB_OWNER` | autodetected | GitHub username/org |
| `AUTO_COMMIT` | `true` | Commit local changes before push |
| `COMMIT_MESSAGE` | auto-generated | Custom commit message |

## Cursor hook

A `stop` hook in `.cursor/hooks.json` also runs publish automatically when an agent session ends. Check `/tmp/shadow-llm-proxy-publish.log` if publish fails silently.

## On failure

If publish fails due to missing auth, tell the user to run `gh auth login` or set `GH_TOKEN`, then rerun `./scripts/publish-to-github.sh`.
